<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If I ran the crypto enforcement unit at the US=
 Securities and Exchange Commission, and I were as crypto-skeptical as the =
actual SEC seems to be, I guess I would want my cases to divide roughly eve=
nly into two categories:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Important cases against big crypto pr=
ojects and, especially, crypto exchanges, cases that will set important pre=
cedents and have large impact on the crypto industry. <a href=3D"https://li=
nk.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/34176316.282398/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21=
iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDYtMDcvd2hlbi1pcy1hLXRva2VuLW5vdC=
1hLXNlY3VyaXR5P2NtcGlkPUJCRDAxMzAyNF9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmd=
XRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTI0MDEzMCZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlz=
dHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBceaf44d1" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=
=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: =
none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; bo=
rder-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  Enforcement actions ag=
ainst=C2=A0<em>exchanges</em></a>, in particular, are likely to have huge e=
ffects: If you shut down crypto=C2=A0<em>trading=C2=A0</em>at centralized e=
xchanges, you get a lot more consumer-protection bang for your buck than if=
 you have to shut down every questionable crypto project individually.</li>=
=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Dumb easy cases against wild scams.</l=
i>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Category 2 is important for a couple of reason=
s. For one thing, those cases are fun for the lawyers. Also you=E2=80=99ll =
probably win. Also people=C2=A0<em>do=C2=A0</em>seem to lose a lot of money=
 to wild crypto scams, and it=E2=80=99s nice to get some back for them.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">For another thing, those cases=C2=A0<em>do=C2=
=A0</em>set good precedents: If you bring a securities fraud case against a=
n absolutely wild scam, the scammers will probably say =E2=80=9Cno no no, w=
e were not doing=C2=A0<em>securities fraud</em>, because our scam tokens we=
re not=C2=A0<em>securities.</em>=E2=80=9D But that argument won=E2=80=99t=
=C2=A0<em>go over well with a judge</em>, who will be inclined to say =E2=
=80=9Cah come on, you were doing a scam, I=E2=80=99m not gonna let you off =
on a technicality=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94=C2=A0and so the judge will be more lik=
ely to rule that the tokens were securities.=C2=A0It is perhaps not a coinc=
idence that we have discussed two big crypto cases that are going on in New=
 York federal courts right now, one against Ripple Labs Inc., which sold in=
vestors tokens that are down a modest 66% from their 2021 peak, and the oth=
er against Terraform Labs Pte, which sold investors tokens that are down a =
dreadful 99.9999% since their 2022 peak, and whose founder is <a href=3D"ht=
tps://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/34176316.282398/aHR0cHM6Ly9kZWN=
yeXB0LmNvLzIxMDI3Ny90ZXJyYS1kby1rd29uLWV4dHJhZGl0aW9uLW1vbnRlbmVncm8/607f07=
ceef4b8524a319a23cB4c1ad79a" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope"=
 target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !importan=
t; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-st=
yle: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> in jail in Montenegro</a>.<a class=3D=
"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-1" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decorat=
ion: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #00000=
0; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: transparent !imp=
ortant; display: inline-block;">
<span>[1]</span>
</a>=C2=A0Both Ripple and Terra have argued that their tokens are not secur=
ities; Ripple=E2=80=99s argument on that point <a href=3D"https://link.mail=
.bloombergbusiness.com/click/34176316.282398/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLm=
NvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDctMTQvcmlwcGxlLWlzLWEtc2VjdXJpdHktYW5kL=
Wl0LWlzbi10P2NtcGlkPUJCRDAxMzAyNF9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRt=
X3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTI0MDEzMCZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHV=
mZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB99b5e237" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"=
itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none=
 !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border=
-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  has mostly succeeded</a>, =
while <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/34176316.282=
398/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDgtMDM=
vdGVycmEtaXMtdXN1YWxseS1hLXNlY3VyaXR5P2NtcGlkPUJCRDAxMzAyNF9NT05FWVNUVUZGJn=
V0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTI0MDEzMCZ1d=
G1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB59b41716" itemprop=
=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #0=
00000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-b=
ottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">=
  Terra=E2=80=99s has failed</a>. Ripple may or may not have a better=C2=A0=
<em>legal=C2=A0</em>argument, but it definitely has a better=C2=A0<em>look=
=C2=A0</em>than Terra.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Also, just, the more hilarious crypto frauds t=
he SEC can sue, the better is its broad argument,=C2=A0to courts and legisl=
ators and the public, that =E2=80=9Ccome on, someone needs to regulate cryp=
to, and nobody else is doing it, so you might as well let us.=E2=80=9D If t=
he SEC finds one ludicrous fraud a week in the crypto space, it is harder t=
o argue that the SEC should just leave crypto alone.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Anyway here=E2=80=99s a <a href=3D"https://lin=
k.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/34176316.282398/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdv=
di9uZXdzL3ByZXNzLXJlbGVhc2UvMjAyNC0xMQ/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB0c3b4209" i=
temprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"co=
lor: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; b=
order-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: =
#ccc;">dumb crypto enforcement case</a> from the SEC against a barely crypt=
o thing called=C2=A0HyperFund:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The Securities and Exchange Commission today c=
harged Xue Lee (aka Sam Lee) and Brenda Chunga (aka Bitcoin Beautee) for th=
eir involvement in a fraudulent crypto asset pyramid scheme known as HyperF=
und that raised more than $1.7 billion from investors worldwide.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">According to the SEC=E2=80=99s complaint, from=
 June 2020 through early 2022, Lee and Chunga promoted HyperFund =E2=80=9Cm=
embership=E2=80=9D packages, which they claimed guaranteed investors high r=
eturns, including from HyperFund=E2=80=99s supposed crypto asset mining ope=
rations and associations with a Fortune 500 company. As the complaint alleg=
es, however, Lee and Chunga knew or were reckless in not knowing that Hyper=
Fund was a pyramid scheme and had no real source of revenue other than fund=
s received from investors. In 2022, the HyperFund scheme collapsed and inve=
stors were no longer able to make withdrawals.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">From <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbus=
iness.com/click/34176316.282398/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9maWxlcy9saXRpZ2F=
0aW9uL2NvbXBsYWludHMvMjAyNC9jb21wLXByMjAyNC0xMS5wZGY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a2=
3cBa48d6431" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blan=
k" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom=
-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; back=
ground-color: #ccc;"> the complaint</a> this case does seem like one that w=
as just fun for the lawyers:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One of the details Chunga touted was the fact =
that Lee and another one of the Founders were featured and interviewed in a=
n episode of an Amazon Prime documentary series called =E2=80=9CNext: Block=
chain.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In one presentation, Chunga leveraged HyperFun=
d=E2=80=99s Founders=E2=80=99 public-facing profiles in order to persuade i=
nvestors that there was no risk in investing with the HyperTech Group: =E2=
=80=9CSome people say things, how do we know they won=E2=80=99t just take o=
ur money and disappear? Well, ladies and gents, they have more to lose than=
 to gain. They=E2=80=99re all over CNN. They have publicly traded companies=
, they are on Amazon Prime, their faces are everywhere. They have more to l=
ose than to gain.=E2=80=9D</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">There was a pivot to the metaverse:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In the fall of 2021, HyperFund reb=
randed itself as HyperVerse. HyperVerse was officially launched on December=
 5, 2021. Part of the new HyperVerse narrative was that the HyperTech Group=
 was creating a virtual world to connect people in the HyperVerse Ecosystem=
, which you would enter using your virtual avatar.</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Speaking of virtual avatars, apparently its CE=
O was fake?</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">During this launch event, which to=
ok place live online and was recorded and then made available publicly onli=
ne, HyperVerse presented a new supposed CEO of HyperVerse,=C2=A0=E2=80=9CSt=
even Reece Lewis.=E2=80=9D In a recorded video played during the launch eve=
nt, Lewis thanked everyone for their participation and for giving him =E2=
=80=9Cthe chance to share more about HyperVerse, our operations, and future=
 direction . . . . =E2=80=9D After repeatedly invoking a prominent social m=
edia company=E2=80=99s rebranding, =E2=80=9CCEO Lewis=E2=80=9D explained th=
at HyperVerse offered a =E2=80=9Cvirtual world=E2=80=9D with =E2=80=9Cnew b=
usiness opportunities=E2=80=9D and the development of a crypto asset, chara=
cterized as a =E2=80=9Cnative token,=E2=80=9D called =E2=80=9CHVT.=E2=80=9D=
 In reality, the person presented as Lewis was an actor playing a role of a=
 fabricated character. He was not the CEO of HyperVerse.</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">There is very little discussion of Hyperfund=
=E2=80=99s technology or token economics, and I=E2=80=99m not sure it had a=
ny. Its technology was telling people that if they invested money in its bu=
siness, it would give them way more money in return. That=C2=A0<em>does=C2=
=A0</em>sound like a securities offering, doesn=E2=80=99t it?</p>
