<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Advertising giant Publicis Groupe SA made an u=
nusual executive hire in mid-2022 =E2=80=93 a lion-headed digital avatar na=
med Leon who would serve as =E2=80=9Cchief metaverse officer,=E2=80=9D guid=
ing clients through the virtual realm that had seized real-world attention.=
</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">His moment in the spotlight didn=E2=80=99t las=
t long.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Five months later, ChatGPT debuted, and the bu=
zz that had surrounded the metaverse ever since Mark Zuckerberg rebranded F=
acebook as Meta Platforms Inc. shifted to artificial intelligence. Leon and=
 other, human officers focused on the metaverse =E2=80=94 an immersive digi=
tal reality where people can interact with one another =E2=80=94 quickly be=
came an endangered species. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Instead, businesses are scrambling to appoint =
AI leaders, with Accenture and GE HealthCare making recent hires. A few met=
averse executives have even reinvented themselves as AI experts, deftly swi=
tching from one hot technology to the next. Compensation packages average w=
ell above $1 million, according to a survey from executive-search and leade=
rship advisory firm Heidrick &amp; Struggles. Last week, Publicis said it w=
ould invest 300 million euros ($327 million) over the next three years on a=
rtificial intelligence technology and talent.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I mean, if your chief metaverse officer was an=
 imaginary digital lion, (1) firing him is fine, he won=E2=80=99t be upset,=
 he doesn=E2=80=99t need this job to feed his virtual cubs,=C2=A0and (2) su=
rely your new chief artificial intelligence officer should be a chatbot? It=
 is truly incredible how intense and how brief the whole =E2=80=9Cmetaverse=
=E2=80=9D thing was:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CIt=E2=80=99s been a long time since I=
 have had a conversation with a client about the metaverse,=E2=80=9D said F=
awad Bajwa, the global AI practice leader at the Russell Reynolds Associate=
s executive search and advisory firm. =E2=80=9CThe metaverse might still be=
 there, but it=E2=80=99s a lonely place.=E2=80=9D =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Most companies have largely moved on from the =
metaverse. The word was uttered just twice on earnings calls at S&amp;P 500=
 businesses last quarter, compared with 63 times in 2022=E2=80=99s first qu=
arter, according to Bloomberg transcript data. That year, eight out of ten =
CEOs said they were either hiring dedicated talent with expertise in the sp=
ace or expanding the responsibilities of their leadership teams to cover it=
, according to Russell Reynolds. All were chasing a piece of a global busin=
ess opportunity that McKinsey &amp; Co. consultants at the time optimistica=
lly estimated could be worth $5 trillion by 2030.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">You could imagine three skill sets here:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Metaverse skills: I don=E2=80=99t kno=
w, designing digital lion avatars or whatever.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-b=
ottom: 5px;">AI skills: understanding how modern artificial intelligence mo=
dels work, how to build them, how to deploy and use them, etc.</li>=09<li s=
tyle=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Internal politics and entrepreneurship: unders=
tanding that saying =E2=80=9Cmetaverse=E2=80=9D would get you a big job and=
 budget and bonus in 2022, but saying =E2=80=9CAI=E2=80=9D will get you tho=
se things in 2024. What magic word will get you those things in 2026? Proba=
bly somebody will know before I do.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">My assumption is that Skill 1 was valuable in =
2022 and Skill 2 is valuable in 2024, though I can=E2=80=99t be sure; I hav=
e no particular evidence that the chief metaverse officers hired in 2022 we=
re in fact any good at doing metaverse stuff. (Was the lion?) And my assump=
tion is that Skill 3 is sort of permanently valuable, perhaps more so the m=
ore trends and technologies change.=C2=A0</p>
